Business Brief -- Telefonos de Mexico S.A.:
   Phone Company Posts Gain
   Of 78% in Its 1991 Profit
In New York Stock Exchange trading, Telmex American
depositary shares jumped $2.875 to $57.875.
   The company said consolidated operating revenue for the
year was 16.273 trillion pesos, an inflation-adjusted rise of
21% from 1990.
   Telmex also said it added 670,000 access lines in 1991,
raising the total number of lines in service to 6,024,814, an
increase of 12.5% from 1990.